pitrery: Point-In-Time Recovery (PITR) tools for PostgreSQL


FEATURES
--------

pitrery is set of tools to ease to management of PITR backups and
restores:

- Management of WAL segments archiving with compression to hosts
  reachable with SSH or on the local machine

- Automation of the base backup procedure

- Restore to a particular date

- Management of backup retention


QUICK SETUP
-----------

1. Get the source

2. Edit the config.mk

3. Run make and make install

4. Configure WAL archiving:

   - Edit archive_xlog.conf

5. Copy pitr.conf to a new file to configure a particular backup

6. Edit this file to fit your system

7. Run pitr_mgr to perform your backups


DEVELOPMENT
-----------

The source code is available on github: https://github.com/dalibo/pitrery

Tarballs are located on https://dl.dalibo.com/public/pitrery/

